<section xml:id="grading-scheme" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title> Grading Overview</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
        <table><title>Grading Scheme Table</title>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>
        10%
      </cell>
      <cell>
        Homework Assignments
      </cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>
        15%
      </cell>
      <cell>
        Engagement &amp; Reflections
      </cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>
        15%
      </cell>
      <cell>
        Quizzes
      </cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>
        30%
      </cell>
      <cell>
        Midterms (Celebrations of Learning)
      </cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>
        30%
      </cell>
      <cell>
        Final Exam
      </cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>
</table>
        The maximum grade cutoff for any flavor of A will be 90%, 80% for any flavor of B, 70% for any C 
        and 60% for any D. Plusses and minuses will be assigned at the discretion of the instructor at 
        the end of the semester.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <subsection xml:id="Celebrations-of-Learning-description">
    <title>Celebrations of Learning</title>
    <p>
        There will be 3-5 Celebrations of Learning throughout the semester, including a cumulative Final, which are opportunities to display your 
        mastery of the skills we will practice in class. There will be no make-up assessments for these. If you think you will need to miss 
        such an assignment, you may be permitted to take the exam early but you must work this out with me beforehand. Unless 
        otherwise noted, you will work on these on your own, and will not be permitted use use any outside resources.

        <table>
	<title>Proposed Exam Dates</title>
	<tabular>
		<row>
			<cell>
				Exam 1
			</cell>
			<cell>
				Feb 18
			</cell>
		</row>
		<row>
			<cell>
				Exam 2
			</cell>
			<cell>
				March 23
			</cell>
		</row>
		<row>
			<cell>
				Exam 3
			</cell>
			<cell>
				April 22
			</cell>
		</row>
		<row>
			<cell>
				Final Exam
			</cell>
			<cell>
				Varies By Section
			</cell>
		</row>
	</tabular>
</table>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="quizzes-description">
    <title>Quizzes</title>
    <p>
        Through the semester you will be asked to complete quizzes over material during class. Unless otherwise noted: you will work on these on 
        your own, will not be permitted to use any outside resources, and they must be completed in class. 
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="homework-description">
    <title>Homework Assignments</title>
    <p>
        Homework will be assigned, collected and graded regularly through MyLab. 
        You are encouraged to work collaboratively on your homework assignments, however, 
        the work you turn in must be your own and any collaboration must be acknowledged. 
        In addition to the assigned exercises from the text, your daily assignment is to read the appropriate section of the text before class.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="reflections-description">
    <title>Reflections</title>
    <p>
        At various points in the semester, you will be asked to reflect on your progress, the class, and your skills as a learner. 
        There will be assignments that require you to think about these things, and respond to some prompts about them. 
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="engagement-description">
    <title>Engagement</title>
    <p>
        Since your participation is expected you should do your best to participate well.  This includes asking questions during group discussions 
        and while you are working in groups, and may also include taking a turn to write on the board.  Simply attending class every day and working 
        with your group mates will likely earn you somewhere between 60% and 70% as an engagement grade, so you should do your best to be an active 
        participant in the discussions that will come up as we wrestle with new concepts. 
    </p>
  </subsection>
</section>